verbose_text: Only 6 of 38 men with PSA level> = 3.0 ng/mL considered low-risk and therefore not advised to be referred were, however, referred to the urologist by their GP. Within the available FU time, in two of these men GS 3 +3 PCa was detected, resulting in an overall negative predictive value (NPV) of 96% for any PCa and 100% NPV for csPCa.
